@startuml system-deployment
title Ecommerce Platform - UML Deployment Diagram

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam wrapWidth 220
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Shopper\nweb browser / mobile" as Shopper
actor "Software Engineer\nXP + GenAI tools" as Engineer
actor "Platform Engineer" as PlatformEngineer
actor "Support and Operations" as Operations

cloud "External Systems" as ExternalSystems {
  component "Identity Provider" as ExternalIdentity
  component "Payment Gateway" as ExternalPayment
  component "Email / SMS Provider" as NotificationProvider
}

frame "Azure Production Environment" as AzureProd {
  node "Azure Edge" as AzureEdge {
    node "Azure Front Door\n+ CDN" as FrontDoor
    node "Web Application Firewall" as Waf
    node "AKS Ingress Controller" as Ingress
  }

  node "Azure Kubernetes Service\nCluster: ecommerce-prod\nExecution environment: containers" as Aks {
    artifact "Validated image tags\nand Kubernetes manifests" as DeploymentArtifacts
    component "Ecommerce service workloads\nQuarkus containers\nBFF, API gateway, domain services, workers" as EcommerceWorkloads
  }

  frame "Managed Data Services\nPrivate Link" as DataServices {
    database "PostgreSQL data stores\nprofile, product, search, cart,\npricing, order, saga, inventory, delivery" as PostgresStores
    queue "Kafka Backbone\nTopics: order.created, payment.authorized,\nstock.reserved, slot.booked" as KafkaTopics
  }

  frame "Shared Azure Platform Services" as SharedAzure {
    storage "Key Vault\nmanaged identities" as KeyVault
    component "Observability\nAzure Monitor, App Insights,\nLog Analytics" as Observability
    component "Private DNS" as PrivateDns
    component "Azure Policy" as AzurePolicy
    storage "Backup Vault" as BackupVault
  }
}

frame "Software Delivery Pipeline" as DeliveryPipeline {
  node "Git Repository\ntrunk + branches" as GitRepository
  node "Pull Request\nreview + checks" as PullRequest
  node "CI/CD Pipeline\ncompile, tests, scans, SBOM" as CicdPipeline
  storage "Artifactory\nMaven/cache\nrelease bundles" as Artifactory
  storage "Docker Registry\nACR or JFrog Docker" as DockerRegistry
  node "CD Pipeline\nGitOps / deploy automation" as CdPipeline
}

Shopper --> FrontDoor : HTTPS storefront traffic
FrontDoor --> Waf : edge routing
Waf --> Ingress : filtered HTTPS traffic
Ingress --> EcommerceWorkloads : route customer-facing requests
DeploymentArtifacts --> EcommerceWorkloads : run as container workloads

EcommerceWorkloads --> ExternalIdentity : login integration
EcommerceWorkloads --> ExternalPayment : payment authorization
EcommerceWorkloads --> NotificationProvider : transactional notifications
EcommerceWorkloads --> PostgresStores : read/write service-owned data
EcommerceWorkloads --> KafkaTopics : publish and consume domain events
EcommerceWorkloads --> KeyVault : retrieve secrets
EcommerceWorkloads --> Observability : emit logs, metrics, and traces

Engineer --> GitRepository : commit and push short-lived branch
GitRepository --> PullRequest : PR opened or updated
PullRequest --> CicdPipeline : run validation checks
CicdPipeline --> Artifactory : restore dependencies and publish artifacts
CicdPipeline --> DockerRegistry : build, scan, sign, and push images
DockerRegistry --> CdPipeline : validated image tags
CdPipeline --> Aks : GitOps deploys manifests and validated images
CdPipeline --> DeploymentArtifacts : materialize release in AKS

PlatformEngineer --> CicdPipeline : maintain delivery templates and release policy
PlatformEngineer --> SharedAzure : manage Azure platform services
Operations --> Observability : diagnose alerts and dashboards
DataServices --> PrivateDns : private name resolution
DataServices --> BackupVault : backups
AzurePolicy --> Aks : production policy controls

legend right
Source: examples/diagrams/deployment/system-example-cicd-pr-model.md
Default view hides AKS internal service complexity behind aggregate workloads.
GitOps deploys validated artifacts to Azure Kubernetes Service.
Only topology facts explicitly described by the source document are represented.
Ports are omitted because the source describes HTTPS and internal service traffic
but does not assign concrete port numbers.
endlegend

@enduml
